<h1 id="content">Infrared.h</h1>

<article>

    <p id="articleTitle"></p>
    <p id="article">
        This header file handles all infrared sensor data.
    </p>

    <p id="article">
        The infrared sensor has two methods of reading input. The first one is using the direct mod
        e; however, the more usefule one is the zone method. there are five zones, for the directio
        n in which each reads in, please consult the paper shipped with your IRv2 sensor unit. This 
        file offers many ways to reduce annoyances in reading infrared values via rounding or ignor
        ing values below a certain threshold. Both of these functions are useful in filtering out a
        ny possible noise the sensor may pick up on; however, it should be noted that these alone w
        ill not filter out all noise.
    </p>

    <p id="article">
        Only members which are meant to be accessed, called, or started in the cases of fields, met
        hods, and tasks, respectively, are shown, some members may be excluded.
    </p>

</article>

