<article>

    <p id="articleTitle">Method Overview</p>

    <p id="methodDoc">
        <code>%bool% initInfrared( %tsensors% infrared )</code><br/>
        Initializes the passed infrared sensor to read for an F.T.C. competition.<br/>

        This will attempt to initialize the IR sensor to read a 1200 Hertz infrared signal ten time
        s. Each attempt will be followed by 100 milliseconds of waiting time before the next attemp
        t. Upon a tenth failure, the NXT will play the exception sound.<br/>

        <table border="0" id="parameters">
            <col width="250"/>

            <tr>
                <th>Parameter</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>

            <tr>
                <td>%tsensors% infrared</td>
                <td>The ifnrared sensor to initialize.</td>
            </tr>

        </table>

        <table border="0" id="parameters">
            <col width="250">

            <tr>
                <th>Returns</th>
            </tr>

            <tr>
                <td>%true% if the initialization of the sensor succeeded, %false% if it did not.</td>
            </tr>

        </table>

    </p>

    <p id="methodDoc">
        <code>%void% updateInfrared( %tsensors% infrared )</code><br/>
        Reads and updates zone readings from the given infrared sensor.<br/>

        Reads the direct and zone values fromt he ifnrared seeker. Then if a zone reading is less t
        han the threshold sets the zone reading to zero. After checking to ensure that the rounding 
        number is greater than one, each zone is rounded to the enartest multiple of <code>irRoundi
        ng</code>

        <table border="0" id="parameters">
            <col width="250"/>

            <tr>
                <th>Parameter</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>

            <tr>
                <td>%tsensors% infrared</td>
                <td>The ifnrared sensor to read from</td>
            </tr>

        </table>
    </p>

